eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 60 Years
Maximum age: 100 Years
This trial does not accept healthy volunteers.
Have adequate archival prostate cancer tissue for DNA analysis

Potential participants for whom serum creatinine levels are unknown, or for whom serum creatinine values are not current within four weeks prior to the imaging visit, will be excluded unless a laboratory test confirming normal kidney function (GFR > 60) can be obtained before the date of the imaging appointment

groups.description: Patients participate in structured health education and support group sessions over 60 minutes once per week for 20 weeks. Patients then participate in support group sessions for 32 weeks.
groups.name: Group II (attention-control intervention)

groups.description: Patients undergo FGD-PET/CT scan within 4 weeks of start of treatment and after 18 fractions of EBRT. Patients also undergo EBRT QD for 5 days per week for 6 weeks, and receive erlotinib hydrochloride PO QD on days 1-28. Courses repeat every 28 days for 1 year in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitor

groups.name: Group I (EGFR Mutation)

groups.description: Patients receive erlotinib hydrochloride PO QD and celecoxib PO BID on days 1-30. Courses repeat every 30 days for up to 6 months in the absence of disease progression or unacceptable toxicity.

interventions.name: Drug, Food, Chemical or Biomedical Material
Epidermal Growth Factor Receptor Tyrosine Kinase Inhibitor

groups.name: Treatment (erlotinib hydrochloride and celecoxib)

outcome_measures.measure: To evaluate the safety, pharmacokinetics (PK), and pharmacodynamics (PD) of orally administered PLX8394 in patients with advanced solid tumors [Part 1]

outcome_measures.analysis_method: Descriptive statistics such as frequencies and percentages will be used to aid in the evaluation of EBV and HHV-8 gene expression patterns.
